summary: This script is running a DOS command to launch QEMU, a virtual machine emulator, for an Android emulation. It checks if the latest version is required and specifies memory allocations and disk image file. The provided path references indicate the locations of relevant files on the system.

details.comment: This script is running a DOS command to launch QEMU, a virtual machine emulator, for an Android emulation. It checks if the latest version is required and specifies memory allocations and disk image file. The provided path references indicate the locations of relevant files on the system.
details.content:
@echo off
REM do we need latest?
REM "D:\Program Files (x86)\Android\android-sdk\tools\qemu\windows-x86_64\qemu-system-x86_64.exe"  -enable-hax -m 2M,maxmem=5M -mem-path R:\ -hda c.hd -boot d
"E:\Program Files\qemu\qemu-system-x86_64.exe" -accel hax -m 2M,slots=2,maxmem=5M  -hda c.hd -boot d
REM "D:\Android\SDK\emulator\lib\pc-bios"
REM D:\Program Files (x86)\Android\android-sdk\tools\lib\pc-bios\kvmvapic.bin
REM this is not native one.
